main_body:
The production and marketing rules referred to in Article 7(1)(a) of Regulation (EC) No 104/2000 shall include the following elements:
(a) the quality, size or weight and presentation of products offered for sale;
(b) sampling, receptacles used for sales purposes, packaging and labelling and the use of ice;
(c) the conditions of the first placing of the market, which may include rules on the rational disposal of production in order to stabilise the market.

Where a Member State decides to extend certain rules adopted by a producers' organisation to non-members, the notification to the Commission referred to in Article 7(3) of Regulation (EC) No 104/2000 shall include at least:
(a) the name and address of the producers' organisation concerned;
(b) all the information required to show that the organisation is representative, particularly by reference to the criteria set out in Article 1;
(c) the rules in question;
(d) the justification for these rules, supported by appropriate data;
(e) the geographical area in which it is intended to make these rules obligatory;
(f) the duration of the rules;
(g) the date of entry into force.
